ind:Offering rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Service ;
    rdfs:label 'Offering' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master catalog of all water and wastewater service offerings available to customers, including potable water supply, wastewater collection, recycled water, fire protection, irrigation, and bulk water services. Defines the canonical service type, delivery mode, applicable customer classes (residential, commercial, industrial, municipal), regulatory tariff reference, connection fee schedule, service tier options, and lifecycle status. This is the SSOT for what Water Utilities offers in the market and the anchor entity for rate schedules, SLAs, and service agreements.' .

ind:ServiceRateSchedule rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Service ;
    rdfs:label 'Service Rate Schedule' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Defines the approved tariff rate structures for each service offering, including tiered volumetric rates (with tier thresholds, unit prices, and tier sequences), flat fees, demand charges, seasonal rate adjustments, and minimum charges. Captures the rate case approval date, effective and expiration dates, regulatory authority, rate code, applicable customer class, and billing unit of measure. Tier definitions (inclining block, declining block, uniform) are maintained as structured components within each schedule. Supports rate case modeling and regulatory tariff compliance. Aligned with Oracle CC&B rate schedule configuration. [SSOT: Canonical rate schedule definition; billing.billing_rate_schedule references this as SSOT]' .

ind:Territory rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Service ;
    rdfs:label 'Territory' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Defines the geographic service territories and franchise areas within which Water Utilities is authorized to provide water and wastewater services. Includes territory boundaries (GIS polygon references via Esri ArcGIS), regulatory franchise agreement identifiers, applicable state primacy agency jurisdiction, service type coverage (potable, wastewater, recycled), and territory classification (urban, suburban, rural). Supports tariff applicability and regulatory reporting.' .

ind:ServiceClass rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Service ;
    rdfs:label 'Service Class' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reference classification of customer service classes used for rate application and regulatory reporting, such as Residential Single-Family, Residential Multi-Family, Commercial, Industrial, Irrigation, Fire Protection, Municipal, and Wholesale. Each class carries a class code, description, applicable rate schedule group, billing cycle type, and regulatory reporting category. Aligned with PUC tariff classification and AWWA customer class standards.' .

ind:Agreement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Service ;
    rdfs:label 'Agreement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Represents the active contractual relationship between Water Utilities and a customer account for a specific service offering at a service location. Captures agreement start and end dates, contracted service class, applicable rate schedule, minimum usage commitments, deposit requirements, special conditions, and agreement status. This is the SSOT for what service a customer account is enrolled in. Aligned with Oracle CC&B service agreement entity.' .

ind:Point rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Service ;
    rdfs:label 'Point' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Represents the physical location where a utility service is delivered to a customer, corresponding to a metered connection point on the distribution or wastewater network. Captures the service point address, GIS coordinates (Esri ArcGIS), service type (potable water, wastewater, recycled water), connection size (pipe diameter in inches), pressure zone, DMA assignment, and active status. Links the commercial service agreement to the physical network infrastructure.' .

ind:ConnectionApplication rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Service ;
    rdfs:label 'Connection Application' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks customer applications for new service connections, service upgrades, disconnections, and transfers. Captures application date, requested service type, service address, applicant details, connection size requested, estimated flow demand (GPM), application status, review milestones, fees assessed, and approval or rejection details. Supports the new service onboarding workflow and capacity planning. Aligned with Microsoft Dynamics 365 field service request intake.' .

ind:Order rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Service ;
    rdfs:label 'Order' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Operational work orders issued to field crews for service-related activities including new service turn-ons, turn-offs, reconnections after non-payment, meter sets, service upgrades, and final reads. Captures order type, scheduled date, completion date, assigned crew, service point reference, work performed, and outcome status. Distinct from asset maintenance work orders (owned by asset domain). Aligned with Oracle CC&B field activity and Microsoft Dynamics 365 field service.' .

ind:SlaDefinition rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Service ;
    rdfs:label 'Sla Definition' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Defines the service level agreements applicable to each service offering or service class, including response time commitments for outages, restoration time targets, water quality guarantee parameters, pressure guarantee thresholds (PSI), and customer notification requirements. Captures SLA type, metric name, target value, measurement unit, regulatory basis (SDWA, state rules), and penalty or credit terms for non-compliance. Supports regulatory tariff compliance and customer service commitments.' .

ind:Tariff rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Service ;
    rdfs:label 'Tariff' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record of regulatory tariff filings and associated rate case proceedings with the Public Utilities Commission or state regulatory authority. Captures the full lifecycle from rate case filing (test year, requested revenue requirement, hearing dates, intervenor parties) through approval (final order, approved revenue requirement) to the effective tariff (tariff number, effective date, tariff type, incorporated rate schedules and service rules). This is the regulatory anchor for all rate and service term compliance, linking rate case proceedings to their resulting approved pricing structures. Supports financial planning, regulatory compliance, and rate modeling.' .

ind:ServiceRateCase rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Service ;
    rdfs:label 'Service Rate Case' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks the lifecycle of regulatory rate case proceedings filed with the Public Utilities Commission or state regulatory authority to adjust water and wastewater service rates. Captures filing date, test year, requested revenue requirement, approved revenue requirement, rate case status, hearing dates, intervenor parties, final order date, and the resulting approved tariff reference. Supports financial planning, regulatory compliance, and rate modeling. [SSOT: governed by finance.finance_rate_case] [DEPRECATED: Single source of truth is finance.finance_rate_case]' .

ind:SpecialContract rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Service ;
    rdfs:label 'Special Contract' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records negotiated special service contracts with large industrial, municipal, or wholesale customers that deviate from standard tariff terms. Captures contract type (industrial user, wholesale, intergovernmental), negotiated rate terms, minimum volume commitments (MGD), demand charge structure, contract duration, renewal terms, special conditions (IUP compliance, pretreatment requirements), and regulatory approval status. Distinct from standard service agreements governed by published tariffs.' .

ind:ConservationProgram rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Service ;
    rdfs:label 'Conservation Program' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master catalog of customer programs including water conservation programs (rebates, tiered pricing incentives, water audits, drought surcharges), demand management programs, and customer affordability/assistance programs (lifeline rates, PIPP, bill discounts, emergency assistance). Captures program name, program type, eligibility criteria (including income thresholds for affordability programs), incentive or benefit structure, funding source, program period, target outcomes, enrollment tracking, and regulatory mandate reference. Supports AWWA water efficiency goals, state conservation mandates, and regulatory affordability requirements.' .

ind:AffordabilityPlan rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Service ;
    rdfs:label 'Affordability Plan' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Defines the low-income customer assistance and affordability programs available, including lifeline rates, percentage-of-income payment plans (PIPP), bill discount programs, and emergency assistance funds. Captures plan name, eligibility income thresholds, discount percentage or fixed credit amount, maximum benefit duration, funding source, regulatory mandate, and enrollment capacity. Supports equitable access to essential water services and regulatory affordability requirements.' .

ind:BulkWaterAgreement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Service ;
    rdfs:label 'Bulk Water Agreement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records negotiated special service agreements with large industrial, municipal, wholesale, or intergovernmental customers that deviate from standard published tariff terms. Covers wholesale bulk water supply, industrial user contracts, intergovernmental agreements, and special pricing arrangements. Captures agreement parties, contract type, negotiated rate terms, volume commitments (MGD), demand charge structure, delivery specifications (pressure, quality), take-or-pay provisions, contract duration, renewal terms, special conditions (IUP compliance, pretreatment requirements), emergency supply terms, and regulatory approval status. Distinct from standard retail service agreements governed by published tariffs.' .

ind:OfferingTerritoryAvailability rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Service ;
    rdfs:label 'Offering Territory Availability' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the availability and authorization of specific water and wastewater service offerings within defined geographic service territories. It captures the regulatory approval, rate adjustments, and lifecycle management of which offerings are available in which territories. Each record links one offering to one service_territory with attributes that exist only in the context of this territory-specific availability, including territory-specific rate adjustments, franchise authorization dates, and availability status that cannot be stored on either the offering or territory alone.. Existence Justification: Water utilities operate service offerings across multiple geographic territories, each with distinct franchise agreements, regulatory approvals, and rate structures. A single offering (e.g., potable water supply) is made available in multiple territories (Downtown District, North County, etc.), and each territory offers multiple service types (potable, wastewater, recycled water). The utility actively manages which offerings are available in which territories, with territory-specific rate adjustments, regulatory authorizations, and lifecycle states that cannot be stored on either the offering or territory entity alone.' .

ind:ServiceProgramEnrollment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Service ;
    rdfs:label 'Service Program Enrollment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the enrollment relationship between a billing account and a conservation program. It captures the participation of a customer account in a specific water conservation program, tracking enrollment lifecycle, incentive payments received, and water savings achieved. Each record links one billing account to one conservation program with attributes that exist only in the context of this enrollment relationship.. Existence Justification: In water utility operations, billing accounts (customers) can simultaneously enroll in multiple conservation programs (toilet rebate, irrigation audit, rain barrel incentive, drought surcharge programs), and each conservation program serves many billing accounts. The utility actively manages these enrollments as operational business entities, tracking enrollment lifecycle, processing incentive payments, measuring water savings per account-program combination, and verifying eligibility. This is not an analytical correlation but an operational business process where enrollment records are created, updated, and closed by program administrators. [SSOT: Canonical program enrollment; customer.customer_program_enrollment references this as SSOT] [SSOT: governed by customer.customer_program_enrollment] [DEPRECATED: Single source of truth is customer.customer_program_enrollment]' .

ind:ProgramMaterialEligibility rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Service ;
    rdfs:label 'Program Material Eligibility' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the eligibility relationship between conservation programs and materials. It captures which materials (fixtures, devices, equipment) are eligible for rebates or incentives under specific conservation programs. Each record links one conservation program to one eligible material with program-specific rebate amounts, quantity limits, and eligibility periods that exist only in the context of this program-material combination.. Existence Justification: Conservation programs in water utilities offer rebates and incentives for multiple eligible materials (high-efficiency toilets, smart irrigation controllers, low-flow fixtures, etc.). Each material can be eligible under multiple programs simultaneously (e.g., a WaterSense toilet may qualify for both a general water efficiency program and a low-income assistance program). The utility actively manages this eligibility catalog, setting program-specific rebate amounts, quantity limits, and eligibility periods for each program-material combination to support customer enrollment and budget tracking.' .

ind:PfasCompoundMaster rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Quality ;
    rdfs:label 'Pfas Compound Master' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master reference table for pfas_compound_master. Referenced by pfas_compound_id.' .

